  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging wiki: https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/wiki/debugging -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3AConsenSys/Teku -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nUse case: \r\n`EpochProcessor.processFinalUpdates(MutableBeaconState state):`\r\n```java\r\n    state.setPrevious_epoch_attestations(state.getCurrent_epoch_attestations());\r\n    state.getCurrent_epoch_attestations().clear();\r\n```\r\nHere the `state.getCurrent_epoch_attestations()` is an ssz list which is aimed to be 'moved' from the `current_epoch_attestation` filed to the `previous_epoch_attestation` field. \r\nThe issue is that this is a mutable list acquired 'by reference' and after the first line the same instance is shared by both `current_epoch_attestation` and `previous_epoch_attestation` fields. The second line effectively clears both fields. \r\n\r\nThe right code would be either \r\n```java\r\n    state.setPrevious_epoch_attestations(state.getCurrent_epoch_attestations().commitChanges());\r\n    state.getCurrent_epoch_attestations().clear();\r\n```\r\nor (is not currently allowed but might be fixed): \r\n```java\r\n    state.setPrevious_epoch_attestations(state.getCurrent_epoch_attestations());\r\n    state.setCurrent_epoch_attestations(\r\n        BeaconState.CURRENT_EPOCH_ATTESTATIONS_FIELD_SCHEMA.get().getDefault());\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe question is: should we somehow handle or disallow the original case or leave it for the client code to sort out? ",
